  "story": "Sarah Flower Adams, an English Unitarian poet, wrote this hymn in 1841 based on the story of Jacob's dream at Bethel in Genesis 28. The tune BETHANY by Lowell Mason (1856) is the most widely used in America. The hymn is famously associated with the sinking of the Titanic in 1912; survivors reported that the ship's band played it as the vessel went down, though accounts vary.",
  "lyrics": {
    "structure": [
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "lines": [
          "Nearer, my God, to Thee,",
          "Nearer to Thee!",
          "E'en though it be a cross",
          "That raiseth me;",
          "Still all my song shall be,",
          "Nearer, my God, to Thee,",
          "Nearer, my God, to Thee,",
          "Nearer to Thee!"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "lines": [
          "Though like the wanderer,",
          "The sun gone down,",
          "Darkness be over me,",
          "My rest a stone;",
          "Yet in my dreams I'd be",
          "Nearer, my God, to Thee,",
          "Nearer, my God, to Thee,",
          "Nearer to Thee!"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "lines": [
          "There let the way appear,",
          "Steps unto heaven;",
          "All that Thou sendest me,",
          "In mercy given;",
          "Angels to beckon me",
          "Nearer, my God, to Thee,",
          "Nearer, my God, to Thee,",
          "Nearer to Thee!"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "lines": [
          "Then, with my waking thoughts",
          "Bright with Thy praise,",
          "Out of my stony griefs",
          "Bethel I'll raise;",
          "So by my woes to be",
          "Nearer, my God, to Thee,",
          "Nearer, my God, to Thee,",
          "Nearer to Thee!"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "lines": [
          "Or if, on joyful wing",
          "Cleaving the sky,",
          "Sun, moon, and stars forgot,",
          "Upward I fly,",
          "Still all my song shall be,",
          "Nearer, my God, to Thee,",
          "Nearer, my God, to Thee,",
          "Nearer to Thee!"
        ]
      }
    ]
